   <S PAR='164' RSNT='1' SNO='164'>When you see that God s speaking is different from yours, that His work is different from yours, and that the places He wants to go are different from the places you want to go, you will be dissatisfied with His arrangements and begin to argue with Him, asking why He is doing these things.</S>
   <S PAR='165' RSNT='1' SNO='165'>You will begin to be angry with God and misunderstand Him.</S>
   <S PAR='166' RSNT='1' SNO='166'>It may never occur to you that a servant of the Lord will encounter these things.</S>
   <S PAR='167' RSNT='1' SNO='167'>But to your surprise, they will take hold of you.</S>
   <S PAR='168' RSNT='1' SNO='168'>These things will not be a part of your plan, but they will fill your environment, school, home, and office.</S>
   <S PAR='169' RSNT='1' SNO='169'>As a result, you will begin to argue with God and blame Him.</S>
